OL,3,CPeople given more time to repay #330
OL,4,Cmillion Covid tax bill in Jersey
OL,6,FPeople in who paused their prior-year
OL,7,Ftax payments in 2020 have been given a
OL,8,Ftwo-year extension to decide how they
OL,9,Fwill settle their outstanding bills.
OL,11,FDuring the , around #330 million of
OL,12,F2019 tax liabilities were frozen for
OL,13,Ffuture repayment to help support many
OL,14,Fworkers and those who are self-
OL,15,Femployed.
OL,17,FJersey's Treasury Minister, Deputy
OL,18,FElaine Millar, says she will push back
OL,19,Fthe start of the statutory repayment
OL,20,Fscheme from 2025 to 2027 for those
OL,21,F'Prior Year Basis' taxpayers.
